The paper discusses the inventive design process and how it affects technological performance trends. This topic is closely related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves understanding how humans interact with technology. The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic analogical transfers, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for problem-solving. The model presented in the paper involves the assimilation of individual operational ideas in components of artifacts, which is similar to the systems engineering (cs.SY) approach. The paper also discusses the differences in interactions among components for different domains, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper suggests further empirical research, which is a common theme in cybernetics (cs.CY).
